bibdata.title: Index all incremental dumps created since the most recent full dump

comments.body: Yeah we can't have one incremental run before another either. To handle this I think we'd have to either check to make sure there aren't started DumpFiles from an earlier dump enqueued or have some sort of managing coordinator in the database.

Hm. A managing coordinator in the database seems tricky when you want to manage building a new index on catalog-alma-rebuild. A given incremental file may have been indexed into the live prod index but not into the rebuild index, or vice-versa.

firestone_locator.title: Port Bibdata over Voyager Item Call to Bibdata over Alma Call to Obtain Normalized Call Number and other Metadata

comments.body: Blocked by issue #45.

The item call needs to move to this route path: https://bibdata-alma-staging.princeton.edu/bibliographic/{MMS_ID}/holdings/{holding_id}/availability.json

The top level solr call needs to move to:
https://catalog-alma-qa.princeton.edu/catalog/9941150973506421/raw

(Currently this goes to bibdata for real-time solr like data, but I think maybe we can avoid that which causes an extra hit to the alma api this time around).
This appears to have been done already, via this PR: https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/commit/a71d5d459192c518a4dc37610995d881ead19f64
